gomodel:SYNGO_3098  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.5: \"Nrx3-C1ql2/3 Signaling Recruits KARs in Cultured Hippocampal Neurons\"\n- \"To define the roles for Nrx3-C1ql2/3 interactions in organizing KAR-containing synapses, we expressed Nrx3β+SS525b together with C1ql2 and C1ql3 (C1ql2+3) on the surface of HEK293 cells and cocultured them with C1ql2/3 null hippocampal neurons. We found that endogenous GluK2/3, as well as neuroligin 1 (NL1, a receptor that binds to all Nrx isoforms) and PSD95, accumulated in hippocampal neurons contacting HEK293 cells (Figure 5A). However, when Nrx3β+SS525b was expressed without C1ql2+3, NL1 and PSD95, but not GluK2/3, formed clusters in C1ql2/3 null hippocampal neurons (Figure 5A). \"\n\nNote: the role of C1ql2/3 is further detailed in other figures of the paper.. Experimental description: Endogenous C1ql2, C1ql3, and GluK2/3 immunoreactivities in WT hippocampus. Arrows indicate CA3 stratum lucidum. Insets show immunoreactivity in mice\nlacking a corresponding gene to confirm antibody specificity. (Legend Fig. 1A, p. 754)\n- Overexpressed Nrx3 is of mouse species: \"a set of constructs for Mus musculus Nrx3β (+SS4+SS5)-ectodomain (RefSeq: NP_001239003.1\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" ;
        dc:date           "2018-04-30" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3098" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

